    {
      "id": "PopularPost139578",
      "post_content": "Ah shoot, roguepariah points out that artifact lands don't trigger this. I saw the word \"play\" (instead of \"cast\"), got all excited and just stopped reading apparently. =(  \n  \nOne or two of these guys combined with a few [Etherium Sculptor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Etherium Sculptor)s can let you tear through your deck. While the mana cost is a bit high, the card advantage he can provide in the right deck is invaluable, especially if you're using [Crystal Ball](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crystal Ball) or another method of scry to sift through any unwanted cards. Still, I always struggle with how many to include in my decks, since you really never want more than 2 out, and sometimes eve more than 1 can really murder your library. Seems like usually the best way to go is to use a few of these to compliment a main draw engine unless you're really confident you can avoid discarding half your library a turn later.",
      "posted_by": "Lyoncet",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost139578\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">Ah shoot, roguepariah points out that artifact lands don't trigger this.  I saw the word \"play\" (instead of \"cast\"), got all excited and just stopped reading apparently. =(<br/><br/>One or two of these guys combined with a few <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Etherium Sculptor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Etherium Sculptor\">Etherium Sculptor</a>s can let you tear through your deck.  While the mana cost is a bit high, the card advantage he can provide in the right deck is invaluable, especially if you're using <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Crystal Ball\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crystal Ball\">Crystal Ball</a> or another method of scry to sift through any unwanted cards.  Still, I always struggle with how many to include in my decks, since you really never want more than 2 out, and sometimes eve more than 1 can really murder your library.  Seems like usually the best way to go is to use a few of these to compliment a main draw engine unless you're really confident you can avoid discarding half your library a turn later.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '139578'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy54409\">Lyoncet</span>\r\n                                (3/15/2011 9:08:33 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
